	<entry>
		<title>Cache-Friendly B+Tree Nodes With Dynamic Fanout</title>
		<link href="https://jacobsherin.com/posts/2025-08-18-bplustree-struct-hack/"/>
		<updated>2025-08-18T00:00:00Z</updated>
		<id>https://jacobsherin.com/posts/2025-08-18-bplustree-struct-hack/</id>
		<content type="html">&lt;p&gt;If a B+Tree node has to fit into the cpu cache, the memory layout has to be a single contiguous block. This memory layout requires low-level control which increases the complexity of the implementation, but is a necessary trade-off for higher performance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Memory Layout of a B+Tree Node&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;language-text&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-text&quot;&gt;  +----------------------+&lt;br /&gt;  | Node Header Metadata |&lt;br /&gt;  +----------------------+&lt;br /&gt;  | node_type            |  &lt;-- Inner or Leaf Node&lt;br /&gt;  | max_size             |  &lt;-- Maximum Entries Per Node (fanout)&lt;br /&gt;  | node_latch           |  &lt;-- RW-Lock&lt;br /&gt;  | end_ptr              |  &lt;-- Past-the-end pointer&lt;br /&gt;  +----------------------+&lt;br /&gt;  | Node Data            |&lt;br /&gt;  +----------------------+  &lt;-- Data Elements (key-value)&lt;br /&gt;  | data[0]              |&lt;br /&gt;  | data[1]              |&lt;br /&gt;  | data[2]              |  &lt;-- end_ptr: if current size = 2&lt;br /&gt;  | ...                  |&lt;br /&gt;  | data[N]              |  &lt;-- N = max_size - 1&lt;br /&gt;  +----------------------+&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;nav class=&quot;toc&quot; aria-labelledby=&quot;toc-heading&quot;&gt;
  &lt;h2 id=&quot;toc-heading&quot;&gt;Table of Contents&lt;/h2&gt;
